{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "b7e3a1d4-5f28-4c9a-8b6e-1d3f5a7c9e2b",
		"name": "Smart Redact Manager API",
		"description": "API collection for the Smart Redact Manager Service.\n\n## Usage\n\n1. **Upload a PDF** -- Use \"Upload PDF File\" (local) or \"Upload File from URL\" to upload a document. The `pdfFileId` and `pdfDekToken` are saved automatically.\n2. **Run SI Detection** -- Use one of the SI Detection requests (sync or async). The `jobId`, `fdfFileId`, and `fdfDekToken` are saved automatically.\n3. **Poll async results** -- If using async mode, call \"Get SI Detection Result\" until the job completes.\n4. **Download the FDF** -- Use \"Download FDF File\" to get the redaction annotations.\n5. **(Optional) Edit and re-upload the FDF** -- Modify the FDF and use \"Upload Modified FDF File\" to upload it back.\n6. **Run SI Redaction** -- Start a redaction job with the PDF and FDF. The `redactedPdfFileId` and `redactedPdfDekToken` are saved automatically.\n7. **Download the redacted PDF** -- Use \"Download Redacted PDF\" to get the final result.\n\nAll IDs and tokens are propagated automatically via test scripts -- just run the requests in order.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
